Implement 3-Way Payment Flow Logic (Cashier System Refactor):

🔵 1. Staff-order Individual Payment
Trigger: single order from staff-order
Action:
Mark order as PAID
Update database only for that order
Hide only that order in UI
Result:
Table status = available ONLY if no other active orders exist
🟣 2. Staff-order Merged Tables Payment
Trigger: merged tables from staff-order (e.g. 3-4)
Action:
Mark all orders in table_ids as PAID
Update all related tables in database
Hide merged card (e.g. “3-4”)
Result:
All involved tables become available ONLY when no other active orders remain
🟡 3. Group Reservation Payment (type = group)
Case A: No individual orders in group tables
Example: group 3-4-5 only has group order
Action:
Pay group reservation via reservation_id
Mark group as PAID
Hide group card (3-4-5)
Update all tables → set to available
Case B: Has individual orders inside group tables
Example: table 3 in group 3-4-5 has extra order
Flow:
Individual order exists → shown in “Individual Tables”
Pay individual order:
Mark only that order as PAID
Hide only that order
DO NOT release table yet
Pay group reservation:
Check remaining unpaid individual orders in group
If ALL cleared:
Mark group as PAID
Hide group card
Set all tables (3-4-5) → available
⚠️ Core Rules (IMPORTANT)
Never release table if ANY unpaid order still exists (group or individual)
Group payment and individual payment are independent but share final table state
Table becomes “available” only when:
Group is paid (if exists)
AND all individual orders are paid
🎯 Expected Result
No cross-update between flows
Group + Individual can coexist safely
Table only becomes free when ALL related payments are completed